content: I do not have access to the most recent and up-to-date information about the real estate market and its impact on local businesses in new york city. however, some sources suggest that the covid-19 pandemic has affected both the residential and commercial real estate market in the city. many businesses have closed down or shifted to remote work, leading to lower demand for office space. additionally, there has been a decline in tourism and business travel, which has impacted the hospitality industry and related businesses. however, some experts also note that there could be opportunities for investors and homebuyers to take advantage of lower prices in certain neighborhoods.
